cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.CV 

This paper proposes a new method for reinforcement learning that addresses the challenge of generalization in domains where the optimal value function cannot easily be reduced to a low-dimensional representation. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), systems and control (cs.SY), and computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV). The paper specifically focuses on deep reinforcement learning and Atari games, which further supports the likelihood of these sub-categories.
